Preview of vol. 2 at http://antipastohw.blogspot.com/2010/01/open-source-hardware-book-volume-2.html

"While there are many books out there that examine and dissect the nature of the software and tools that allow people to build Open Source Hardware, there hasn't been nearly as much discussion about the fact that hardware and tinkering in the "real world" with real components costs "real" money. So this volume is about the economics side of Open Source Hardware, and about the "business models" people are experimenting with."


